    ],
    "summary": "On May 29, 2021 at approximately 05:00 hours, during rigging up for sidetrack operations on the A005 well at MC Block 773, the Toolpusher was scoping the lower intermediate derrick section when the drill line came free from the drawworks. The traveling block and fast line fell to the drill floor. The area was designated a red zone with no personnel within 15 feet, resulting in no injuries or equipment damage. Root cause was inadequate length of drill line spooled on the drum.",
    "recommendations": [
      "JSA should identify hazards and mitigations for spooling drill line inside drawworks",
      "MODS 140 rig up procedures should include steps for installing drill line"
    ],
    "key_phrases": [
      "inadequate length of drill line",
      "drawworks drum",
      "traveling block",
      "scoping derrick",
      "red zone",
      "no personnel within 15 feet"
    ]
